1 whole of an organism, but there is no requirement for instruction on human development
2 from conception to birth; and
3 WHEREAS, the use of high definition ultrasound video and computer-generated
4 animation showing the development of vital organs in the early stages of human fetal
5 development is being incorporated into instruction across the country in courses concerning
6 human biology.
7 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
8 urge and request the State Board of Elementary and Secondary Education to incorporate the
9 science of human growth and development, including instruction on prenatal growth and in
10 utero development of all vital organs and significant markers and cell growth, into the state
11 content standards for the subjects of science or health education at an age- and grade-
12 appropriate level.
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the legislature urges and requests the State
14 Board of Elementary and Secondary Education to provide age- and grade-appropriate
15 materials and information on its website that may be used in curriculum and instruction
16 related to the standards, including high definition ultrasound video or computer-generated
17 animation that depicts prenatal growth and development.
18 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the legislature urges and requests the State
19 Board of Elementary and Secondary Education to submit a written report to the House
20 Committee on Education and the Senate Committee on Education not later than
21 March 1, 2027, relative to any action taken with respect to the content standards and the
22 clearinghouse as requested in this Resolution.
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
24 president of the State Board of Elementary and Secondary Education and the state
25 superintendent of education.
